Filters.
    - Filters are used to format the application data.

    - we have two types of filters.
        1. Predefined Filters
        2. Custom Filters

Predefined Filter.

        - The Filters Given by the Framework called as Predefined Filters.

1. uppercase
    - used to convert the lowercase characters to uppercase.

Ex.
    $scope.var_one="hello";
    {{var_one}} //hello
    {{var_one | uppercase }} //HELLO


2. lowercase
    - used to convert the uppercase characters to lowercase

Ex.
    $scope.var_two = "HELLO";

    {{var_two}}  //HELLO
    {{var_two | lowercase}} //hello


3. currency
    - used to append the "$" symbol to the Numerical Values.

Ex.
        $scope.var_three = 100;

        {{var_three}} //100
        {{var_three | currency }} //$100.00

4. date
    - used to format the date accroding to application requirement.

Ex.

    $scope.var_four = new Date();

    {{var_four}}

    {{var_four | date:'dd-MM-yy'}}
    {{var_four | date:'MM-dd-yyyy'}}
    {{var_four | date:'short'}}
    {{var_four | date:'medium'}}
    {{var_four | date:'fullDate'}}
    {{var_four | date:'shortTime'}}
            ---
            ---
            ---

5. orderBy
    - used to arrange the data either in assending order / decending order.

6. limitTo
    - used to display required number of records from an array.

7. filter
    - used to search the array based on users input.

$scope.array = [{'id':1,'name':'AngularJS','rank':1},
                {'id':5,'name':'Kotlin','rank':5},
                {'id':2,'name':'Angular4','rank':2},
                {'id':4,'name':'NodeJS','rank':4},
                {'id':3,'name':'reactJS', 'rank':3}];

             <table border=1>
                <tr>
                    <th>id</th>
                    <th>name</th>
                    <th>rank</th>
                </tr>
                <tr ng-repeat="x in array | orderBy:'-id' |
                                            limitTo:3 |
                                            filter:'AngularJS'">
                    <td>{{x.id}}</td>
                    <td>{{x.name}}</td>
                    <td>{{x.rank}}</td>
                </tr>
             </table>
